==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chimæra
<hw>Chi*m⟦ae⟧"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Chimera</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A cartilaginous fish of
several species, belonging to the order <ord>Chimaeriformes</ord> of the
class <class>Holocephali</class>. The teeth are few and large. The head
is furnished with appendages, and the tail terminates in a
point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>Note: more information and an image is available at:
<a href="http://www.fishbase.org/Summary/SpeciesSummary.cfm?genusname=Chimaera&speciesname=monstrosa">Fishbase - chimaera</a>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chimaeroid</ent>⟦br⟧
